term: F-Droid
---
definition:

F-Droid is a repository of FOSS (free and open source software) applications for android. 
Just like google play one can browse, install and keep track of updates on the device using F-Droid and it is provided by [The Guardian Project](../the-guardian-project).
Tor Browser is available on F-Droid. Follow these [steps](https://tb-manual.torproject.org/mobile-tor/) if you prefer installing the app through F-Droid.

